        "Optional:",
        "",
        "The default behaviour is, that the document will be saved, when the editor is destroyed, i.e. the page is closed. Note, that Ivy closes a page only on process end or a task switch.",
        "",
        "Calling forcesave will speed this up a little bit by requesting an immediate save even with an open editor. Nevertheless saving is always done asymchronously and may take a few seconds.",
        "",
        "If you need the updated document immediatly after editing, you can wait some time or implement some marker in your own OnlyOfficeDocumentHandler to check if the file was already saved by the last editor."
